Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.99,0:00:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The most crucial moment in life is during decision making.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.00,0:00:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.17,0:00:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But also instilled \Nnumerous lessons on how to live.{unsure, lit is "for the sake of living, precepts, numerous left behind"}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.39,0:00:31.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,700)\c&H0007DF&\fs100\b1\bord0\blur1}Animentary\N{\b\c&HE0DBF3&}Decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.21,0:00:42.98,Default,,0,0,30,,Wit is your weapon{honestly no clue what is megurase here, deepl says "rack one's brain"}\NRemember to use your head{智恵をめぐらせ 頭を使え}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.98,0:00:50.95,Default,,0,0,30,,Repress your anguish, \NIf you are a man{悩み抜け抜け 男なら}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.95,0:00:58.66,Default,,0,0,30,,One decision is enough \NTo make others cry or laugh{泣くも笑うも 決断ひとつ}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.66,0:01:06.69,Default,,0,0,30,,If you win, don't hold your head high, \NIf you lose, don't cry{勝っておごるな 敗れて泣くな}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.69,0:01:14.55,Default,,0,0,30,,Men, don't you ever let others see your tears{男 涙は見せぬもの}
Comment: 0,0:01:34.91,0:01:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.51,0:01:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A large invasion force, led by General MacArthur
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.76,0:01:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,was approaching the coast \Nof the Filipino island of Leyte.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.35,0:01:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,On October 20th, 1944, \Nas the troops were just about to disembark,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.15,0:01:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,General MacArthur announced the landings \Nfrom on board the cruiser Nashville. {declaration; proclamation; announcement - probs means to the locals}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.57,0:02:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a moving moment for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.18,0:02:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,On March 11th, 1942,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.60,0:02:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,having promised them, "I shall return" \Namidst starvation and a rain of Japanese shells,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.11,0:02:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,he bid farewell to his subordinates \Nand Filipino refugees on the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.57,0:02:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,2 years and 7 months passed since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.31,0:02:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}General MacArthur speaking. {http://www.emersonkent.com/speeches/i_have_returned.htm}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.89,0:02:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}People of the Philippines:{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.68,0:02:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I have returned.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.45,0:02:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I have returned!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.27,0:02:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}By the grace of Almighty God our forces stand again on Philippine soil, consecrated in the blood of our two peoples...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.03,0:02:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese were now determined to challenge the \NUS Fleet that they spotted previously to a decisive battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.22,0:02:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,For that, the contingency plan Sho Part 1 that was being developed for the previous 2 months, was activated.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.21,0:02:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Kurita's Division of the Combined Fleet \Nwas dispatched on a mission
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.82,0:02:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to destroy the American transport fleet \Ncurrently in Leyte Gulf.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.19,0:03:04.16,Sign,,0,0,200,,{\fade(0,400)\c&HE9ECEB&\b1\blur1\bord0}Episode 21\N{\fs100}Battle of Leyte Gulf (Part 1)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.88,0:03:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Stationed in Brunei Bay in British Borneo, Kurita's 2nd Fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.84,0:03:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,complied with the Commander-in-Chief of the Combined Fleet Toyoda's orders to infiltrate the Leyte Gulf on the 25th
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.61,0:03:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and held a strategy meeting \Nwith all the ships' captains present.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:21.92,0:03:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,As you may already know, \Nin the upcoming operation,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:26.58,0:03:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the newly formed 3rd Fleet, \Nled by Vice Admiral Ozawa,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:31.06,0:03:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,using the remaining aircraft carriers, \Nincluding Zuikaku, as a decoy,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:35.17,0:03:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,will be deployed in this region \Nin order to draw away Halsey's Force.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:38.34,0:03:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, the 5th Fleet \Nunder Vice Admiral Shima
Dialogue: 1,0:03:42.48,0:03:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,will join forces with our 2nd Southern Fleet \Nat the Surigao Strait, the entrance to Leyte Gulf.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:48.95,0:03:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Kurita's central force under Vice Admiral Kurita, \Nincluding the 1st Night Battle Unit,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:54.44,0:03:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,will infiltrate Leyte Gulf \Nvia the San Bernardino Strait.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:58.63,0:04:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The 2nd Night Battle Unit \Nwill support them from the south.
