Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.81,0:04:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, I got that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.93,0:04:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I can't get behind the goal of attacking \Nthe transport fleet, given in the previous explanation. {not sure what he means by https://jisho.org/word/%E5%BC%95%E3%81%A3%E6%8E%9B%E3%81%8B%E3%82%8B ; was "confused by" in HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.68,0:04:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,For that, a single attack from an aircraft carrier \Nwould be more than enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.23,0:04:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.56,0:04:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the higher-ups thinking?! {chief; main; principal; major}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.75,0:04:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The complete destruction of the enemy's \Nmain combat fleet should be made our #1 priority. {assuming he means "not convoys"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.78,0:04:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, we're being sent to attack the transport fleet? \NDo they really think that it's the best our 2nd Fleet can do? {not sure what he means: 我々第二艦隊を必要な人でも思っているのですか - "Do you even think that we, the Second Fleet, are necessary people?" - could be he means "do they think we're only fit for such unimportant job" or could be "do they think we're useless/unneeded"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.52,0:04:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.66,0:04:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A decisive fleet battle is what it was born for! {lit: ... is our mission}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.08,0:04:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.66,0:04:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, should the enemy's capital ships appear,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.22,0:04:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,we're allowed to suspend our hunt for convoys \Nand focus on attacking those.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.45,0:04:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, the current war situation \Ndoesn't allow for an open engagement. {lit: However, we can no longer afford the the luxury of fighting a flashy battle now - means we have to do a feint and drive the capitals away to attack defenseless convoys, which is sly and not very honest}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.41,0:04:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Musashi's Captain? \NYou've been silent for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.41,0:04:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I stand in opposition to everyone else here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.00,0:05:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It pains me to say so, since I've been entrusted with a ship that was bred for a decisive battle, with her 46 cm cannons...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.55,0:05:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But I believe the age of decisive naval battles \Nended with the Russo-Japanese War.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.78,0:05:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.71,0:05:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Presently, it's the decisive aerial battle \Nthat everything hinges on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.27,0:05:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than glomming onto \Nthe honor of a decisive naval battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.23,0:05:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we should now be concerned \Nwith improving our damage control and offensive abilities. {lit: how can we make the damage smaller and attack power stronger is the question}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.77,0:05:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Even knowing that the enemy's task force \Nhad set up a web,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.64,0:05:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we're heading to Leyte naked, without a single plane \Nto support us - that's what concerns me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.03,0:05:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"Honor," you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.26,0:05:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.70,0:05:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you even saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.55,0:05:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Our navy's traditions are not a joke! {lit: ignoring ... ?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.65,0:05:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That timidity will get us nowhere! {lit: what can you do with such cowardice}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.33,0:05:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.00,0:05:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Say something! Hey! {no clue}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.53,0:05:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen, do I have some amazing news for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.89,0:05:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A special attack corps that'll ram the enemy ships \Nwith 250 kg bombs strapped to their Zeroes was formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.50,0:06:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We've nothing to fear from even a hundred enemy carriers, \Nwith this deadly attack that'll only use fuel for one-way trip. {unsure why so hard wording: without returning home, certain death attack with only enough fuel for one way trip - "without returning home" and "one way trip" is kinda the same thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.04,0:06:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The argument of captains who glommed onto \Nthe decisive battle doctrine
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.92,0:06:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,was finally brought to a definitive end \Nwith the news of the creation of kamikaze corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.51,0:06:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain of the battleship Musashi, Vice Admiral Inoguchi \Nfelt that the notion of a decisive naval battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.30,0:06:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so persistent in the heads of his colleagues and superiors spelled worrisome... No, spelled ill omen in big letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.51,0:06:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.26,0:06:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.08,0:06:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.41,0:06:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.50,0:06:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, what did you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.48,0:06:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We've finished the refueling works.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.61,0:06:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Thanks for your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.05,0:06:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there really something? {guess, not even sure who's saying it}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.46,0:06:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, we're going on a sortie as naked as a jaybird, \Nknowing full well the enemy's air raid is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.40,0:06:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There won't be any decisive battle, \Njust us suffering enormous damage. {unsure what he means: 艦隊決戦なんてものじゃない必ず大きな損害を受ける}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.39,0:06:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.06,0:07:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. No "but" can do. We've got orders. {again unsure: しかし行かなければならない}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.03,0:07:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What's worse, all I can think of is our Musashi. \NAnd I shouldn't be thinking so much. {unsure once more: しかも私はこの武蔵だけしか考えられない考えてはいかんのだ - maybe the last part means "I can't help but to think of it"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.66,0:07:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do, as an executive officer? {act. fukukan is adjutant but later he calls him fukucho and it makes more sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.54,0:07:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow the orders and do whatever is in my powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.34,0:07:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The limits to what I can do are in reducing \Nthe damage to our second fleet as much as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.38,0:07:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.06,0:07:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.55,0:07:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you heard it already? \NA suicide corps - kamikaze.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.61,0:07:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.82,0:07:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They know they won't return alive! {could mean anything: 生還を来さずという / it means without coming back alive}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.30,0:07:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't return alive, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.50,0:07:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Executive Officer Kato. {executive officer (navy)}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.13,0:07:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately repaint the hull and deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.64,0:07:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.84,0:08:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This decision to repaint the ship -
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.98,0:08:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what on earth is it supposed to signify? {what is its meaning}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.26,0:08:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Too slow! Finish that part quicker! {HA's, nc what's after socchi}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.31,0:08:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Warrant officer Arakawa? {was "sergeant"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.45,0:08:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.18,0:08:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it only us who smartens up? {meaning why aren't any other ship repainting; lit: doing cosmetics/decoration}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.91,0:08:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Why aren't others repainting too? {/only us}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.19,0:08:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit shooting the breeze and finish it! \NDon't you two understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.21,0:08:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Our captain is the 4th one we ever had, \Nthe XO is the 2nd. You know that? {nth generation; nth (person to occupy a position, e.g. president)​ - this is musashi's 4th captain indeed so he probs means this; https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E6%AD%A6%E8%94%B5_(%E6%88%A6%E8%89%A6)#%E6%AD%B4%E4%BB%A3%E8%89%A6%E9%95%B7}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.09,0:08:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... So?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.38,0:08:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,4 and 2 make up the word for "burial robe"! {read my tl notes for this episode}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.51,0:08:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.51,0:08:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatcha so shocked about? {lit: what's that face}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.80,0:08:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in the army! \NWe're wearing burial robes at all times. {lit: don't you know we the military men wear ... always - nc whats last word}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.09,0:08:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't forget to change your underwear today! {unsure he means this, kinda makes sense: everyone needs to ...; was "dress" in HA; 今日は下着みんな買いとくんやぞ}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.73,0:08:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The captain already finished preparing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.56,0:08:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, why don't I help as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.07,0:09:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You idiot, quit worrying! {g}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.44,0:09:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you, our Musashi \Nis an unsinkable battleship.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.72,0:09:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,She won't go under. Even after you hit her with 5 or 6 torpedoes, she'll keep running like clockwork! {lit: like on top of a saddle}
Dialogue: 1,0:09:24.42,0:09:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,At 8:00 a.m. on October 22nd, 1944,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.42,0:09:53.41,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HCEE3E5&\bord0.1\blur1\3c&H56A4AE&\pos(711,36)}Luzon
