Dialogue: 1,0:09:28.94,0:09:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,main force of Kurita's fleet of 27 ships, including \NMusashi, Yamato, and Nagato, left Brunei Bay.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:37.16,0:09:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They were to sail west of Palawan Island \Nand south of Mindoro Island.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:41.45,0:09:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then pass through the San Bernardino Strait
Dialogue: 1,0:09:44.00,0:09:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and reach Leyte Gulf \Nby creeping along the eastern coast of Samar.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:47.46,0:09:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This sortie required them to cover \Nabout 1900 km of distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.41,0:09:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,At noon, as Kurita's Fleet was in Palawan Passage, \Nthe Commander-in-Chief of the combined Fleet Toyoda
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.33,0:10:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,sent them a telegram, commending the struggle \Nof the decisive battle force... {not sure what to make of soutou, prolly strife; struggle; conflict; fight​}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.81,0:10:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I want our soldiers to regain their resolve \Nto overcome all hurdles we encounter. {nc what's this shishou isssedaru, was 将兵はここに、師匠一世ざるの覚悟を新たにし in whisper, nothing in HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.20,0:10:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight with purpose - \Nanswer the divine call and beat off a mighty enemy. {no clue whats kouon ni oozubeshi}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.79,0:10:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,However, right off the bat, the Japanese fleet \Nwas spotted by American submarines Dace and Darter. {lit: around this time, even if soon}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.47,0:10:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, can you see anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.98,0:10:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.20,0:10:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,A cruiser, probably?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.02,0:10:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.13,0:10:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,A cruiser, alright. Some destroyers too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.20,0:10:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Plenty of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.05,0:10:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.36,0:10:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.18,0:10:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.10,0:10:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.89,0:10:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A battleship, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.89,0:10:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A real shame we have to sink that baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.45,0:11:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start with the 1st cruiser in line. {ha's}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.35,0:11:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.83,0:11:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready to launch!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.87,0:11:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ready to launch!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.92,0:11:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready to launch!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.94,0:11:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it pretty?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.58,0:11:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. A wonderful sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.34,0:11:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Full to starboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.24,0:11:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though they're the enemy, \Nthey're damn good. {splendid; praiseworthy; admirable; brilliant​}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.60,0:11:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Takao was hit by a torpedo!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.61,0:11:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Depth charges!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.08,0:11:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not depth charges. We hit them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.92,0:11:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,4. 5, 6 hits!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.63,0:12:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There she blows! {/we did it}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.77,0:12:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They got Maya too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.25,0:12:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Launch the rescue. {lit: prepare the rescue/aid}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.28,0:12:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Right off the bat, Kurita's Fleet \Nfulfilled Captain Inoguchi's grim prediction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.69,0:12:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Heavy cruisers Atago and Maya were lost \Nand Takao was severely wrecked.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.73,0:12:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,With many more trouble expected to come \Nin the journey still ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.39,0:13:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Reported sightings of the Japanese fleet off the southern tip of Mindoro by an American patrol plane
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.31,0:13:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,were immediately passed to Admiral Halsey, exercising direct command from the aircraft carrier Lexington.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.22,0:13:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Time - 8:37 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.00,0:13:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Attack! Just attack! There is only the attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.32,0:13:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, with an order from Admiral Halsey, \Nthey Battle of Leyte Gulf started in earnest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.81,0:13:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Launched from aircraft carriers of Bogan's Task Group 38.2 \NIntrepid, Cabot, and Independence,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.69,0:13:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,31 fighters, 16 torpedo bombers, and 12 dive bombers \Nset out to search for Kurita's Fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.27,0:13:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.26,0:13:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like we'll meet them soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.33,0:14:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's a shame that your first time won't even be against a real warship, but you should bear with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.46,0:14:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It was to become her first actual combat deployment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.91,0:14:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's first super-heavy anti-ship gun. The pinnacle of various navy departments' technological advancements.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.96,0:14:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we all ready, locked and loaded? {準備万端相調えもうしそろうか - fully prepared, all arrangements made?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.98,0:14:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The burial robe is also applied.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.53,0:14:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Burial robe?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.04,0:14:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the 4th captain of Musashi, I'm the 2nd XO. \NTogether, 4 and 2 are "death."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.41,0:14:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.89,0:15:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All crew on board also understands how you feel about this, \Nas a captain of the punching bag ship. {sounds like 被害担当官 / "damage control officer", but that doesnt make sense, so it's probs 被害担当艦 / "ship in charge of damage" - meaning the ship that's supposed to take all the damage on herself}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.32,0:15:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, tell them to try to save as many lives \Nas possible, when emergency comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.24,0:15:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.30,0:15:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy naval aviation!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.87,0:15:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Large formation, 90 degrees to the right! {nc whats osshihei, was "horizon / suihei" in ha but that doesn't make sense, they're high above in the next scene}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.27,0:15:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,As the saying goes, in the Ganryujima duel, \NKojiro was the one attacking against the sun. {I think he is talking about https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miyamoto_Musashi#Duel_with_Sasaki_Kojir%C5%8D - Paul}{yeah, gotta be it, but I can't find any records of kojiro attacking against the sun or with his back to the sun etc; in fact, there are so many different versions and accounts of this duel that you can't believe any of them, and I'm not even sure what the last word is, assumed osotte, was "kojiro was the sun" in HA; also, no clue what's the first word, was "in showa era" in HA, but it happened in 1612 / 17th year of Keicho era and showa eras were 834-848, 1312-1317 and 1926-1989, so either it's a script error, or it's not what he means; showa can also be anecdote/brief (comic) story and there are A LOT of anecdotes surrounding miyamoto musashi; here, however, the planes comes from the sun side and musashi is defending so could mean anything, but considering his previous attitude, I'd wager he means "we're at a disadvantage, unlike the other musashi"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.99,0:15:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.05,0:15:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.64,0:15:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.66,0:15:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep firing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.24,0:16:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Please stop! Not the main battery! \NStop firing the main battery!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.09,0:16:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Although a certain shock wave was to be expected \Nwhen firing her 46 cm main battery, {impact; shock; impulse}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.32,0:16:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the actual impact was so strong, \Nit rendered all the other guns on board unusable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.37,0:16:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The traditional decisive naval battle doctrine \Nturned out to be fatally flawed. {lit: it was a miscalculation of Navy's traditional ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.94,0:16:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,However, even after several strafing and torpedo attacks, \NMusashi's performance was unimpaired. {after receiving ... and machine gun fire, functioned completely without loss}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.88,0:16:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The confident appearance of the unsinkable battleship Musashi who simply shrugged off the first torpedo hit
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.62,0:16:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,produced the opposite effect on the American pilots, who now began to target Musashi with rekindled determination.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.72,0:17:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is clearly targeting us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.91,0:17:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Unsurprisingly so. {no clue whatsoever, was "They are coming more and more."}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.27,0:17:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,At 12:30 p.m. 65 aircraft of the 3rd wave and 25 aircraft of the 4th mounted another concentrated attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.89,0:17:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Without any friendly air cover, the naked Musashi ended up \Nreceiving 5 torpedo hits in this concentrate barrage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.04,0:17:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And after 5 more conventional bombs hits, \NMusashi no longer had any life in her. {nc whats seisan, not in HA; lit: seisan on the ship was exhausted/on the breaking point}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.28,0:17:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain Inoguchi was also seriously injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.34,0:17:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, at 2:00 p.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.13,0:17:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,her speed dropped to 6 knots \Nand Musashi left the battle formation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.85,0:17:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If the enemy comes once more, it'll be over for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.68,0:17:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We've no more shells.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.28,0:17:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,No people either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.33,0:17:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Come get your meals!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.94,0:17:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,A meal?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.87,0:17:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that reminds me, \NI've only eaten half of my breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.07,0:17:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You cooked it damn well amidst all this shooting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.74,0:17:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't even have enough hands \Nto form it into rice balls.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.91,0:18:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, whatever, just eat it. \NYou can't do any fighting on an empty stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.95,0:18:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.90,0:18:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.00,0:18:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we can eat now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.80,0:18:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, it really {\i1}is{\i0} good!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.63,0:18:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought I won't get to eat ever again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.14,0:18:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.31,0:18:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm good, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.99,0:18:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what about the night meal?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.78,0:18:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Think we'll make it to the night meal? {lit: do you think our lives will last us until ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.45,0:18:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you wanna live some more?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.41,0:19:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in the end I couldn't do anything to help you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.92,0:19:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.95,0:19:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was rude to you before. Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.44,0:19:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's definitely over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.65,0:19:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Musashi has her limits. {lit: even for musashi of whom a lot was expected}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.93,0:19:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Still no command to abandon ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.22,0:19:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Abandoning ship without an order \Nis a violation of military discipline.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.81,0:19:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Warrant Wakamizu! {no clue what's issui, was soldier in HA, maybe name; *sui is usually something about water/naval}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.65,0:19:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Sugano? {squad leader; divisional officer - here this, but later he is the commander of anti-aircraft subdivision and ranked "captain (Army, US Marine Corps, USAF); lieutenant (Navy); flight lieutenant (RAF, RAAF, RNZAF, etc.)​"}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.18,0:20:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Gather the surviving anti-aircraft gun operators on the aft deck. {act. "machine gun members" but that can only be AA right}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.62,0:20:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir. Roger that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.24,0:20:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Anti-aircraft operators, gather on the aft deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.74,0:20:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it that the 7th anti-aircraft division commander \NLieutenant Sugano had on his mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.78,0:20:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,While he was concerned with saving as many survivors as possible from Musashi, who was dead in the water, {lit: lost her function}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.25,0:20:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,why was the high command taking its time \Nwith the order to abandon ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.15,0:20:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's fierce struggle today was remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.96,0:20:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I thank you for your hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.22,0:20:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it was to no avail, and most of our personnel \Nis either injured or killed, including the 1st gunnery officer. {not sure what to make of "gunnery; artillery chef"; wiki says "anti-aircraft commander, Navy Lieutenant Commander Eisuke Hirose, and senior commander of surveying officer, Navy Captain Takeo Yamada, died in the battle . "}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.16,0:20:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stand the thought \Nof bringing everyone even more suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.25,0:20:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Before long, Musashi will sink.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.76,0:20:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,However, no abandon ship order has been issued.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.34,0:20:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Abandoning ship without an order is shameful for a soldier \Nand against military discipline.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.95,0:20:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, we can't afford increasing our casualties any further!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.52,0:20:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm taking responsibility for all of you, \Nanti-aircraft gunners.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.78,0:21:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Grab whatever you find and flee! {lit: while carrying appropriate/suitable things - means "find something that floats"}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.83,0:21:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This decision saved a great many lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.94,0:21:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,May I?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.00,0:21:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.90,0:21:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I must apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.10,0:21:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave the arbitrary abandon ship order. {/w/o consulting you}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.28,0:21:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Please punish me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.27,0:21:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you did well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.07,0:21:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I was busy writing a last will \Nand missed my chance. {/timing}{He handed Deputy Commander Kato his notebook containing his suicide note and his favorite mechanical pencil, and begged him to live to see what happened to his subordinates. . The vice-commander wished to share his final moments with her, but he was not allowed to do so. }
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.29,0:21:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You knew exactly what I wanted to do. {/understood intentions}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.71,0:21:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.72,0:21:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, my last will is finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.14,0:21:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Executive Officer Kato, please do me the honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.77,0:22:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys hurry up too!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.23,0:22:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, if you excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.23,0:22:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Counting on you. {nc what he means, counting for what?}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.34,0:22:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to follow your example and stay too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.84,0:22:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.34,0:22:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Only me and those unable to leave should stay. {/casualties/dead and wounded}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.24,0:22:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But sir, because I wasn't trying hard enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.25,0:22:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Abandon ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.91,0:22:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an order.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.02,0:22:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to the resolute decision of Lieutenant Sugano, \Na mid-level officer, no time was wasted
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.84,0:22:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and the lives of many sailors were saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.28,0:23:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, Musashi who was once touted as unsinkable, sunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.43,0:23:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Falling victim to the decisive naval battle doctrine, she failed to fulfill the very battleship role she was designed for.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.55,0:23:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As per Vice Admiral Inoguchi's decision,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.49,0:23:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,her sacrifice in the form of becoming a punching bag ship, \Nso to say, helped limit the damage to the fleet as a whole.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.32,0:23:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, the abandon ship order given by Lieutenant Sugano, perceptive of his superiors' intent,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.57,0:23:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that saved many of the sailors' lives is still remembered \Nas a brilliant decision by a mid-level officer. {また上級者の意を汲み多くの人命を救った菅野大尉の退官命令は共に中堅幹部の決断として今なお伝えられている - rest is clear, but no clue what to make of "to convey; to report; to transmit; to communicate; to tell; to impart; to propagate; to teach; to bequeath as a mid-level commander's decision" so added brilliant, kinda assuming they mean "in officer academies etc."; that said, it's incredibly hard to find any info on it at all, this is the only trace I got: https://detail.chiebukuro.yahoo.co.jp/qa/question_detail/q1374836853}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.70,0:23:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, some say that Musashi's captain
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.96,0:23:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Vice Admiral Inoguchi followed her fate \Nand took his own life with a determined harakiri. {actually "brilliant/spectacular" but that's not exactly how you describe "disembowelment; harakiri"}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.04,0:24:07.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,0)}The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.\NBut also instilled numerous lessons on how to live.{太平洋戦争はわれわれに平和の尊さを教えたがまた生きるための教訓を数多くのこしている}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.36,0:24:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese fleet that was supposed to infiltrate Leyte Gulf \Ncame under intense attack from the US Air Fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.37,0:24:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That resulted in sinking of the flagship Atago \Nand battleship Musashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.81,0:24:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese Central Force, led by Vice Admiral Kurita \Nwith Yamato as his flagship
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.36,0:24:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,immediately launches a counterattack, \Nletting all hell break loose off the coast of Samar.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.21,0:24:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Next week's decision, depicting Kurita's puzzling order to reverse course: Battle of Leyte Gulf, Part 2. Don't miss it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.88,0:24:38.70,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 22 \NBattle of Leyte Gulf (Part 2)
Comment: 0,0:24:43.11,0:24:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.95,0:24:48.88,Default,,0,0,50,,If you're a man, let's put your strength to test{男だったら　力を試せ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.88,0:24:52.90,Default,,0,0,50,,If you are a man, keep your hopes sizzling{男だったら　希望(のぞみ)を燃やせ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.90,0:24:57.26,Default,,0,0,50,,If you are a man, don't lose your heart{男だったら　くじけるな}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.26,0:25:05.83,Default,,0,0,50,,Because there's just you and me, a man and a man{俺もおまえも　男と男}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.83,0:25:14.31,Default,,0,0,50,,With crimson blood flowing in our veins all the same{おなじ真赤な　血が通う}
